310 g Chicken Breast, Diced
7 g Applewood Smoke Spice
4 tbsp BBQ Sauce
2 unit(s) Sandwich Bun
170 g Coleslaw Cabbage Mix
2 tbsp Mayonnaise
28 g Dried Cranberries
1 tbsp White Wine Vinegar
1 tbsp Oil*
0.13 tsp Salt*
0.13 tsp Pepper*

Before starting, preheat the broiler to high.
Wash and dry all produce.
Halve buns.
On an unlined baking sheet, arrange buns, cut-sides up. Set aside.

Heat a large non-stick pan over medium-high.
Drain chicken. Spread chicken out on a plate or a clean, flat surface, then season with Applewood Smoke Spice, salt and pepper.
When the pan is hot, add 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) oil, then chicken. Cook for 1-2 min, turning occasionally, until chicken is golden.
Reduce heat to medium. Cook for 3-5 min, stirring often, until chicken is cooked through.**
Remove the pan from heat. Add BBQ sauce, then stir to combine. (TIP: Use two forks to break up any larger pieces of chicken.)

Meanwhile, to a medium bowl, add mayo and vinegar, then season with salt and pepper. Whisk to combine.
To the bowl, add coleslaw cabbage mix and cranberries, then toss to coat.
Broil buns for 1-2 min in the middle of the oven, until golden. (TIP: Keep an eye on them so they don't burn!)

Divide saucy chicken between bottom buns, then top with some coleslaw. Close sandwiches with bottom buns.
Served any remaining coleslaw on the side.